**Operating system or device - Godot version:**
Windows 10, godot version 2.1.2 issue presists in 3.0

**Issue description:**
I setup a basic input function with arrow keys. pressing LEFT, RIGHT, and DOWN, each input was acknowledged. however when i did LEFT, RIGHT, and UP, UP was ignored. i then tested by holding down some letter keys: G, H and L, and all arrow key inputs were ignored


**Steps to reproduce:**
```
func _process(delta):
	if Input.is_key_pressed(KEY_UP) && Input.is_key_pressed(KEY_LEFT) && Input.is_key_pressed(KEY_UP):
		print("this wont appear")
```

alternative:
```
func _input(event):
	if event.type == InputEvent.KEY && !event.is_echo():
		for v in buttons:
			if event.scancode == v:
				if event.is_pressed():
					emit_signal(str(buttons[v],"_key_pressed"))
				else:
					emit_signal(str(buttons[v],"_key_unpressed"))
				get_tree().set_input_as_handled()
```
